<$fill $name="body">

!! Three-layer architecture

* ''Browser UI'' ‚Äî `panel.tid` (3 tabs), `toolbar-button.tid`, `styles.tid`
* ''Action widget'' ‚Äî `<$action-git>` XHR bridge between UI and server
* ''Server routes'' ‚Äî `route.js` (GET), `route-post.js` (POST), `git-utils.js` (shared)

!! Components

|!Component |!Layer |!Role |
|`route.js` |Server |GET ops: log, show, stash-list, stash-show, stash-drop |
|`route-post.js` |Server |POST ops: diff, snapshot, stash-push |
|`git-utils.js` |Server |Shared: `resolveTiddlerPath`, `parseTidFields`, `parseTidBody`, `execGit`, `sendJson` |
|`action-git.js` |Browser |`<$action-git>` widget ‚Äî XHR bridge, writes to `$:/temp/` |
|`panel.tid` |Browser |EditTemplate UI ‚Äî 3 tabs (Diff/Commit/Stash) |
|`toolbar-button.tid` |Browser |Editor toolbar button |

!! Why POST for diff/snapshot/stash-push

The server's `$tw.wiki` may not have the latest browser edits due to syncer polling delay. POST allows the browser to send current draft field values.

!! Diff model

All fields compared uniformly. Server returns `fieldChanges` array with per-field diffs.

!! State tiddlers

* `$:/state/rimir/git-int/<title>` ‚Äî panel open/closed
* `$:/state/rimir/git-int/tab/<title>` ‚Äî active tab
* `$:/temp/rimir/git-int/<title>/<op>` ‚Äî operation response data

!! Security

* No arbitrary paths ‚Äî validates against `$tw.boot.files`
* Input validation ‚Äî hash `/^[a-f0-9]{4,40}$/`, index `/^\d+$/`
* `execFile` with array args ‚Äî no shell injection
* CSRF header required (`X-Requested-With: TiddlyWiki`)

!! Key data flows

* ''Diff'': draft fields ‚Üí POST ‚Üí `git show` ‚Üí compare all fields ‚Üí `fieldChanges`
* ''Per-field revert'': click undo ‚Üí delete/set field on draft ‚Üí re-run diff
* ''Commit'': message ‚Üí POST snapshot ‚Üí write `.tid` ‚Üí `git add` + `git commit` ‚Üí auto-refresh log
* ''Restore'': click restore ‚Üí GET show ‚Üí replace all draft fields (remove absent ones)

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="info">
<$fill $name="body">Field order is preserved when writing `.tid` files to avoid creating false diffs in git.</$fill>
</$transclude>

</$fill>
</$transclude>
